<br>
As my guild's only wizard for quite a long time (until a recent returning member came back), I've always viewed it as my responsibility for getting my guildmates or those who attended our raids away safely.  Yes, we have many druids in my guild and they too group up and port people off, but I have always stayed the longest to make sure everyone gets out safely even to the point of waiting for a half an hour for anyone who link died (if I'm in a safe enough spot).  Generally, if I wait in an unsafe spot, people wait with me and we kill in the area until the link dead person comes back or we feel we've waited a sufficient amount of time.  I've felt very guilty leaving behind someone who went link dead that I didn't realize went link dead so I try to get everyone out after a raid if I have the time and capability to do so.<br>
<br>
In any case, I like group tl to bind. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
